   Education Programs - University Programs
   Postgraduate Internship Program


   The Postgraduate Internship Program provides recent college graduates
   with research experience and opportunities to explore their major
   discipline in a real world environment through involvement with INEEL
   mission-related projects. This program is open to graduates who have
   completed all institutional requirements for a Bachelors, Masters, or
   Doctoral degree from an accredited college or university

   In collaboration with the Inland Northwest Research Alliance,
   postgraduate interns will be administered by Washington State
   University (WSU). The participants will become WSU employees, thereby
   incorporating their appointments and payments into WSU's customary
   policies and procedures.
     * Post-baccalaureate - The Post-baccalaureate program provides the
       participant a bridge to professional employment or continued
       education. Appointments are limited to 1 year.
     * Post-masters - The Post-masters program provides the participant a
       bridge to professional employment or continued education.
       Appointments are limited to 3 years.
     * Post-doctoral - The Post-doctoral program provides the participant
       a bridge to professional employment preferably at the INEEL.
       Appointments are limited to 3 years.

   SELECTION CRITERIA
   Selection of participants is competitive and is based on applicant
   qualifications, interests and compatibility with the needs and
   resources of the INEEL, career goals, references, and the projected
   benefit of the experience to the individual and the INEEL.
   U.S. citizenship is not required. Non-U.S. citizen Interns will have
   restricted access to computer resources and facilities, and limited
   access to information/technologies.

   APPOINTMENT CONDITIONS
   Terms and conditions shall contain special appointment stipulations
   that may include, but not be limited to, an appointment period less
   than 12 months or part-time appointment status. If an appointment is
   full-time, but less than 12 months, the participant will receive
   benefits as identified in the benefits section.

   BENEFITS
   As WSU employees, post-graduates appointees are eligible for WSU's
   complete benefit package, which includes medical insurance, dental
   insurance, insurance for same-sex domestic partners, life insurance,
   and long-term disability insurance, whenever an appointment is for
   longer than 6 months and greater than 50%.
     * Salary (salary may increase after first and subsequent years
       depending on performance)
     * Relocation to INEEL
     * Participation in Medical Plan - WSU complete benefit package
     * Ten Holidays (New Years, Dr. Martin Luther King Birthday,
       Presidents' Day, Memorial Day, Independence Day, Labor Day,
       Veterans'Day, Thanksgiving Day and Friday after Thanksgiving, and
       Christmas Day).
     * Annual Leave - 14.67/hours per month
     * Sick Leave - 8 hours per month

   Note: Participants must take Annual Leave or Time Off Without Pay
   during the INEEL annual work shutdown between Christmas and New Year's
   holidays.

   APPLICATION INFORMATION
   If you are interested in applying for a Post-Graduate Internship, click
   here.
   For more information, send an email message to smithmeadows@wsu.edu.

   Page contact: Karen Hsu, hsukm@inel.gov.

